@node "CanDo_EditAll" "CanDo's EditAll Requester"
@toc "CanDo_Main"
   This requester allows you to manipulate objects or cards.  If this
requester was brought up by the Card system then you can manipulate Cards.
Likewise, if you select one of the object type icons while in @{" Edit " link "CanDo_MPAddEditCopy"} mode,
this requester will allow you to manipulate all objects of that type.

   On the left side of the requester is a list of all the cards or objects.
You can use the buttons on the right side of the requester to Add, Edit,
CopyAs or Delete them.

   You can also, via the arrows, change the order of the cards or objects.
Changing the order will sometimes change the visual render on the card's
window.  For instance, a button object at the top of the list is rendered
before the rest of the buttons in the list.  @{fg highlight}You are not able to adjust the
order of some types of objects.@{fg text}

@endnode

@node "CanDo_CopyAll" "CanDo's CopyAll Requester"
@toc "CanDo_Main"
   This requester allows you to select which object or card to copy into the
copy buffer.
   
   See Also: @{" Copy/Paste System " link "CanDo_MPCopyPaste"}.

@endnode

